    • Method Detail

      • setNotificationInterval

        void setNotificationInterval(@NonNull
                             android.util.Pair<java.lang.Integer,java.lang.Integer> notificationInterval)
        Change the minimum notification interval.
        Parameters:
        notificationInterval - When user changes notification interval ([min, max]in seconds). Min value 0 = never. Pre-fetching is also paused while notification display is disabled.

      • setContentTargets

        void setContentTargets(@NonNull
                       java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.util.Set<java.lang.String>> targetAttributes)
        Provide custom targeting attributes, for example ‘team’ for a sports app, or ‘topic’ for a news app.
        Parameters:
        targetAttributes - Map of content targeting attributes that can be used for targeting of push videos. e.g. { ‘teams’ : ["Liverpool", "Everton"] }. Each key of the Map refers to a particular segmentation target attribute. Zero, or more, values may be specified for each attribute.
        See Also:
        Audience Segmentation

      • setNotificationDisplayActive

        void setNotificationDisplayActive(boolean displayNotifications)
        Activate or de-activate notification display. Pre-fetching is also paused while notification display is disabled.
        Parameters:
        displayNotifications - Notifications will be displayed if true, or not displayed if false.

      • reportContentInteraction

        void reportContentInteraction(java.lang.String videoId,
                              java.lang.String contentGenre)
        Report user's interactions with content in app, so Incoming can learn the user's content preferences for selecting the best videos for notifications. Report only positive reactions.
        Parameters:
        videoId - : video ID that matches the one in CMS, or null if unknown or not a video.
        contentGenre - : genre of the content that the user interacted with, e.g. "action", "comedy". Must match the genre in CMS.

      • isNotificationDisplayActive

        boolean isNotificationDisplayActive()
        Query if notifications are being displayed to the user. Notification display may be activated or de-activated by calling setNotificationDisplayActive(boolean).
        Returns:
        true if notifications are being displayed to the user.

      • getDisplayCandidates

        @NonNull
java.util.List<? extends VideoDescriptor> getDisplayCandidates()
        Retrieve a list of videos that can be shown to a user. The list is filtered according to audience segmentation rules. Expired videos, and videos that are still under embargo are excluded from this list.
        Returns:
        an unmodifiable list of videos that have been fetched. The list is sorted in the order the videos would be displayed to the user at the time the method was called.

      • getPrefetchQueue

        @NonNull
java.util.List<? extends VideoDescriptor> getPrefetchQueue()
        Videos that are available for download. The list is filtered according to audience segmentation rules.
        Returns:
        videos that are available for download

      • getWatchedVideos

        @NonNull
java.util.List<? extends VideoDescriptor> getWatchedVideos()
        Videos that have been watched.
        Returns:
        videos that have been watched.

      • enablePrefetch

        void enablePrefetch(boolean enabled)
        Disable or enable pre-fetching. This can be used to provide a user control to turn download on and off.
        Parameters:
        enabled - true if videos should be fetched.
